  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Programme for Country Partnership Zambia 2021-2026</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Programme for Country Partnership (PCP) Zambia will support the Government of the Republic of Zambia in the implementation of its Vision 2030 and the Eighth National Development Plan (8NDP). The Programme&#x2019;s objective and targeted results have built upon the lessons learned in the implementation of the Seventh National Development Plan (7NDP) and have been well aligned with the relevant national policy framework, and notably with the National Industrial Policy 2018.

The Programme will also serve as the main framework of action for UNIDO to contribute to the implementation of the United Nations Strategic Development Partnership Framework (UNSDPF) 2016-2022 for Zambia and its Addendum as well as the UN Socio-Economic Response Plan guiding the UN efforts to facilitate the post-COVID-19 recovery in the country.

Under the leadership of the Ministry of Commerce, Trade and Industry as the Chair of the PCP National Coordination Body, the PCP will strengthen the existing and forge new partnerships for inclusive and sustainable industrial development of the country, with the main objective of contributing to a diversified, competitive, inclusive and sustainable industrial economy of the Republic of Zambia, and in line with its overall structure into three main focus areas: Value addition, Skills development and Policymaking.</narrative>
  </description>
